 come together here in order to recapture, elaborate, and criticize pre-Cultural Turn and non-Cultural Turn modes of analysing structures of experience, feeling, subjectivity and action in human societies and to highlight the still unexploited possibilities developed among others in the work of scholars such as Norbert Elias, Max Gluckman, Eric Wolf, E.P. Thompson and Raymond Williams.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 0aAnthropologyxMethodology. 0aEthnohistory. 0aHistoriography. 7aSOCIAL SCIENCE / Methodology.2bisacsh1 aCarbonella, August, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGiordano, Christian, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGulliver, P. H., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHandelman, Don, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalb, Don, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aKalb, Don, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aMusante, Patricia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRebel, Hermann, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSider, Gerald, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSilverman, Marilyn, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTak, Herman, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTak, Herman, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt40uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978178238962040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781782389620423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781782389620/original  aEBA_BACKALL  aEBA_CL_SN  aEBA_EBACKALL  aEBA_EBKALL  aEBA_ECL_SN  aEBA_EEBKALL  aEBA_ESSHALL  aEBA_PPALL  aEBA_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter